@page "/"

<PageTitle>SpawnDev.ILGPU — GPU Compute Everywhere</PageTitle>

<div class="hero-section">
    <div class="hero-content">
        <h1 class="hero-title">
            <span class="gradient-text">GPU Compute Everywhere</span>
        </h1>
        <p class="hero-subtitle">Write once, run on WebGPU, WebGL, Wasm, CUDA, OpenCL, and CPU</p>
        <p class="hero-description">
            SpawnDev.ILGPU extends the ILGPU compiler with six parallel backends — three for the browser and three for the desktop — all driven by a single C# codebase.
            In the browser, WebGPU and WebGL dispatch to the GPU while Wasm compiles to multithreaded WebAssembly.
            On desktop, the same kernels run natively on CUDA, OpenCL, and multithreaded CPU.
            Every backend runs off the main thread, keeping your UI responsive.
        </p>
        <div class="hero-buttons">
            <a href="fractals" class="btn btn-primary btn-lg">
                <span class="btn-icon">🎨</span> Fractal Demo
            </a>
            <a href="benchmarks" class="btn btn-secondary btn-lg">
                <span class="btn-icon">⏱️</span> Run Benchmarks
            </a>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="features-section">
    <h2 class="section-title">Six Parallel Backends, One API</h2>

    <h3 class="subsection-title"><span class="subsection-icon">🌐</span> Browser Backends</h3>
    <p class="subsection-desc">GPU and multithreaded compute inside any modern browser — no plugins, no installs.</p>
    <div class="features-grid features-grid-3">
        <div class="feature-card feature-highlight-browser">
            <div class="feature-icon">🎮</div>
            <h3>WebGPU</h3>
            <p>C# kernels transpiled to WGSL and dispatched to the GPU. Supports shared memory, atomics, 64-bit emulation, and auto-detects extensions like <code>shader-f16</code> and <code>subgroups</code> for broadcast &amp; warp shuffle operations.</p>
            <div class="feature-tag">Fastest GPU path</div>
        </div>
        <div class="feature-card feature-highlight-browser">
            <div class="feature-icon">🖼️</div>
            <h3>WebGL</h3>
            <p>C# kernels transpiled to GLSL ES 3.0 and executed on the GPU via Transform Feedback. Works on virtually every browser and device — including mobile, Safari, and older desktops. Full 64-bit emulation support.</p>
            <div class="feature-tag">Widest compatibility</div>
        </div>
        <div class="feature-card feature-highlight-browser">
            <div class="feature-icon">🧊</div>
            <h3>Wasm</h3>
            <p>Kernels compiled to native WebAssembly binary and dispatched to Web Workers for near-native parallel execution. Compatible with every browser that runs Blazor WASM — even with a single worker if SharedArrayBuffer is unavailable.</p>
            <div class="feature-tag">CPU fallback</div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <h3 class="subsection-title"><span class="subsection-icon">🖥️</span> Desktop Backends</h3>
    <p class="subsection-desc">Full-speed native execution for console, WPF, and ASP.NET apps — same kernels, zero code changes.</p>
    <div class="features-grid features-grid-3">
        <div class="feature-card feature-highlight-desktop">
            <div class="feature-icon">🟢</div>
            <h3>CUDA</h3>
            <p>Direct PTX compilation targeting NVIDIA GPUs. Maximum throughput with full hardware access — tensor cores, warp-level intrinsics, and the deepest driver optimization stack available.</p>
            <div class="feature-tag">NVIDIA peak performance</div>
        </div>
        <div class="feature-card feature-highlight-desktop">
            <div class="feature-icon">🔶</div>
            <h3>OpenCL</h3>
            <p>Cross-vendor GPU compute via OpenCL 3.0. Runs on NVIDIA, AMD, and Intel GPUs and integrated graphics. Ideal when CUDA is unavailable or when targeting the broadest desktop hardware.</p>
            <div class="feature-tag">Cross-vendor GPU</div>
        </div>
        <div class="feature-card feature-highlight-desktop">
            <div class="feature-icon">🔵</div>
            <h3>CPU</h3>
            <p>Multithreaded CPU accelerator using the ILGPU runtime. Valuable for debugging kernels with breakpoints, running on headless servers, and as a reliable fallback on machines without a GPU.</p>
            <div class="feature-tag">Debug &amp; fallback</div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="features-grid features-grid-3" style="margin-top: 2.5rem;">
        <div class="feature-card">
            <div class="feature-icon">⚡</div>
            <h3>ILGPU Compatible</h3>
            <p>Use familiar ILGPU APIs — ArrayView, Index1D/2D/3D, math intrinsics, and more.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="feature-card">
            <div class="feature-icon">🔀</div>
            <h3>Auto Backend Selection</h3>
            <p>CreatePreferredAcceleratorAsync() picks the best backend: WebGPU → WebGL → Wasm (browser) or CUDA → OpenCL → CPU (desktop).</p>
        </div>
        <div class="feature-card">
            <div class="feature-icon">🌐</div>
            <h3>Blazor WebAssembly</h3>
            <p>Seamless integration with Blazor WASM via SpawnDev.BlazorJS. No native dependencies.</p>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="code-section">
    <h2 class="section-title">Quick Start</h2>
    
    <div class="steps-container">
        <div class="step">
            <div class="step-number">1</div>
            <div class="step-content">
                <h3>Write Your Kernel</h3>
                <p>Define your computation in standard C# — runs on any backend.</p>
                <div class="code-block">
                    <pre><code><span class="keyword">static void</span> <span class="method">MyKernel</span>(<span class="type">Index1D</span> index, <span class="type">ArrayView</span>&lt;<span class="keyword">float</span>&gt; data)
{
    data[index] *= <span class="number">2.0f</span>;
}</code></pre>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="step">
            <div class="step-number">2</div>
            <div class="step-content">
                <h3>Initialize All Backends</h3>
                <p>Register all parallel backends in one call.</p>
                <div class="code-block">
                    <pre><code><span class="keyword">var</span> builder = Context.<span class="method">Create</span>();
<span class="keyword">await</span> builder.<span class="method">AllAcceleratorsAsync</span>();
<span class="keyword">using var</span> context = builder.<span class="method">ToContext</span>();</code></pre>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="step">
            <div class="step-number">3</div>
            <div class="step-content">
                <h3>Create Best Accelerator</h3>
                <p>Automatically selects the best available backend.</p>
                <div class="code-block">
                    <pre><code><span class="comment">// Priority: WebGPU → WebGL → Wasm</span>
<span class="keyword">using var</span> accelerator = <span class="keyword">await</span> context.<span class="method">CreatePreferredAcceleratorAsync</span>();</code></pre>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="step">
            <div class="step-number">4</div>
            <div class="step-content">
                <h3>Allocate &amp; Transfer</h3>
                <p>Allocate a buffer on the device and copy your data to it.</p>
                <div class="code-block">
                    <pre><code><span class="keyword">float</span>[] data = <span class="keyword">new float</span>[length];
<span class="keyword">using var</span> buffer = accelerator.<span class="method">Allocate1D</span>(data);</code></pre>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="step">
            <div class="step-number">5</div>
            <div class="step-content">
                <h3>Execute &amp; Retrieve</h3>
                <p>Load, run, and read back — same API for all backends.</p>
                <div class="code-block">
                    <pre><code><span class="keyword">var</span> kernel = accelerator.<span class="method">LoadAutoGroupedStreamKernel</span>&lt;<span class="type">Index1D</span>, <span class="type">ArrayView</span>&lt;<span class="keyword">float</span>&gt;&gt;(MyKernel);
<span class="method">kernel</span>((<span class="type">Index1D</span>)length, buffer.View);
<span class="keyword">await</span> accelerator.<span class="method">SynchronizeAsync</span>();
<span class="keyword">float</span>[] results = <span class="keyword">await</span> buffer.<span class="method">CopyToHostAsync</span>&lt;<span class="keyword">float</span>&gt;();</code></pre>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

